      "description": "Build automated OWL compliance monitoring and drift prevention system after L-039 incident (2026-05-17).\n\nBACKGROUND:\n- OWL mandate (CHG-0386) requires tiered thinking: Tier 1=10-15s, Tier 2=3min/300s, Tier 3=5+min/unlimited\n- During v2026.5.12 upgrade (18:01-18:30 AEST), OWL was not strictly followed\n- Symptoms: rushed atoms, no verification gaps between steps, chain-reacted on errors\n- Ken flagged drift at 18:30 AEST requiring immediate remediation\n- LESSONS.md L-039 logged, HEARTBEAT.md updated with self-check\n\nGOAL: Prevent OWL drift through automated detection, alerting, and self-correction mechanisms.\n\n=== SUB-TASKS (5 Stories) ===\n\nSTORY 1: owl-compliance-state.json — Real-time Tracking [Yoda]\n- Create state/owl-compliance-state.json schema\n- Track per-response: tier level, thinking time (estimate vs actual), atom count, pause between atoms\n- Flag when 3+ atoms chained without pause (>30s gap)\n- Flag when error occurs and immediate fix attempted without assessment (>2 rapid reactions)\n- Daily summary: compliance score (0-100%), drift incidents count, self-corrections count\n- Effort: 4 hours\n- Dependencies: None\n- Acceptance: State file auto-updates every response, metrics accurate within 10%\n\nSTORY 2: owl-drift-alert.json — Automated Alerting [Yoda]\n- Create state/owl-drift-alert.json schema\n- Auto-generate alert when drift detected: timestamp, session ID, atoms executed, pause durations, violation type (no-pause | chain-reaction | insufficient-thinking)\n- Heartbeat checks for unacknowledged alerts (>2h old)\n- Surface to Ken via Telegram if unacknowledged\n- Auto-clear after 24h if acknowledged\n- Effort: 3 hours\n- Dependencies: STORY 1 complete\n- Acceptance: Alerts generate within 5s of drift detection, Ken receives within 2h\n\nSTORY 3: YODA_RUNBOOK.md — OWL Verification Procedure [Yoda]\n- Add Section: \"OWL Compliance Verification\"\n- Document per-atom checkpoint requirements (pause, show thinking, assess risk, verify, stop-on-error)\n- Add self-correction protocol: detect drift → insert thinking block → report to Ken → log to LESSONS.md\n- Add escalation path: self-correct → Ken flag → LESSONS.md → CHG\n- Include examples from L-039 incident\n- Effort: 2 hours\n- Dependencies: None\n- Acceptance: Runbook section reviewed and approved by Ken\n\nSTORY 4: scripts/owl-audit.sh — Weekly Compliance Reporting [Forge]\n- Parse session transcripts from state files\n- Calculate: avg pause between atoms (target: >30s for T2, >5min for T3)\n- Calculate: error chain-reaction rate (target: <10%)\n- Calculate: tier compliance % (target: >90%)\n- Generate weekly HTML report (canvas output)\n- Email to Ken every Monday 09:00 AEST\n- Flag agents with repeated drift patterns (>3 incidents/week)\n- Effort: 6 hours\n- Dependencies: STORY 1 + 2 complete\n- Acceptance: First report generated and sent within 14 days\n\nSTORY 5: Agent Training Material — OWL Mandate Acknowledgment [Yoda]\n- Update all T3 agent SOUL.md files with OWL acknowledgment section\n- Include self-check questions in agent system prompts\n- Add OWL compliance to agent health dashboard\n- Quarterly OWL compliance review (triggered by Warden cron)\n- Effort: 3 hours\n- Dependencies: STORY 3 complete\n- Acceptance: All 12 agents have OWL section in SOUL.md, review scheduled\n\n=== EFFORT SUMMARY ===\nTotal: 18 hours\n- Yoda: 9 hours (Stories 1, 2, 3, 5)\n- Forge: 6 hours (Story 4)\n- Buffer: 3 hours (testing, documentation)\n\n=== TIMELINE / MILESTONES ===\nWeek 1 (S4):\n- Day 1-2: STORY 1 (owl-compliance-state.json)\n- Day 3-4: STORY 2 (owl-drift-alert.json)\n- Day 5: STORY 3 (YODA_RUNBOOK.md update)\n\nWeek 2 (S4/S5):\n- Day 1-3: STORY 4 (owl-audit.sh)\n- Day 4-5: STORY 5 (Agent training)\n- Day 5: Integration testing, first report\n\n=== OWNER ASSIGNMENTS ===\n- Yoda (lead): Stories 1, 2, 3, 5, integration\n- Forge: Story 4 (script development)\n- Ken (reviewer): STORY 3 runbook approval, weekly report review\n\n=== DEPENDENCIES ===\n- STORY 1 → STORY 2 (state tracking needed for alerts)\n- STORY 1 + 2 → STORY 4 (alerts needed for audit)\n- STORY 3 → STORY 5 (runbook needed for training)\n- External: OpenClaw v2026.5.12 stable (✅ achieved)\n\n=== DEFINITION OF DONE ===\n- All 5 stories complete and verified\n- owl-compliance-state.json tracking 7+ days of data\n- owl-drift-alert.json generated >0 alerts (proving detection works)\n- First owl-audit.sh report sent to Ken and reviewed\n- All 12 agent SOUL.md files updated with OWL section\n- YODA_RUNBOOK.md OWL section approved by Ken\n- Zero drift alerts unacknowledged for 7 consecutive days\n- CHG logged for completion\n\n=== RISK ASSESSMENT ===\n| Risk | Probability | Impact | Mitigation |\n|------|-------------|--------|------------|\n| Monitoring overhead adds latency | High | Medium | Calibrate thresholds after 2 weeks |\n| False positives (normal fast work flagged) | Medium | Low | Manual review first week, tune thresholds |\n| Agent resistance to OWL constraints | Low | Medium | Frame as quality improvement, not punishment |\n| Forge capacity for Story 4 | Medium | Medium | Defer to S5 if needed, Yoda can prototype |\n\n=== BLOCKERS ===\n- None currently\n- Potential: Forge workload in S4 (infra focus on OC2 prep)\n- Mitigation: Yoda can prototype owl-audit.sh if Forge unavailable\n\n=== ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA ===\n- [ ] STORY 1: owl-compliance-state.json created and populated within 7 days\n- [ ] STORY 2: owl-drift-alert.json auto-generates on drift detection\n- [ ] STORY 3: YODA_RUNBOOK.md OWL section approved by Ken\n- [ ] STORY 4: Ken receives first weekly OWL audit report within 14 days\n- [ ] STORY 5: All T3 agent SOUL.md files include OWL acknowledgment\n- [ ] INTEGRATION: Zero unacknowledged drift alerts for 30 consecutive days\n",
